'''Antonio Tarsia''' (July 28, 1643 <U+2013> 1722) was a Slovenian composer.<ref>Salvator <U+017D>itko, ''Antonio Tarsia'' 1993</ref> 

Tarsia was born in [[Pula]].  He was the major composer of the early Baroque in Ljubljana and left a large amount of Latin sacred compositions.<ref>''Barocco padano: Atti del XII convegno internazionale sulla musica'' Alberto Colzani, Andrea Luppi, Maurizio Padoan - 2002</ref>  He died in [[Koper]].
:''To be distinguished from [[Antonio Tarsia]] (Venice 1662-1739) an Italian sculptor.''

